<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1209,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1281,1306]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Carapace transversely ovate, width-to-length ratio 
<number box="[921,959,1281,1305]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1.4">1.4</number>
; gastric, branchial, cardiac and intestinal regions well separated by wide and deep furrows, but subregions (i.e., 
<number box="[994,1003,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
M+ 
<number box="[1047,1061,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
M+ 
<number box="[1106,1119,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
M; 
<number box="[1162,1171,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
L+ 
<number box="[1205,1219,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
L+ 
<number box="[1254,1266,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
L+ 
<number box="[1300,1314,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
L+ 
<number box="[1349,1362,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="5.0">5</number>
L+ 
<number box="[1396,1410,1317,1341]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="6.0">6</number>
L) more-or-less fused; 
<number box="[378,392,1353,1377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="4.0">4</number>
M distinct, bridging gastric and cardiac regions; carapace vermiculations showing traces of fused granules, anastomosing, forming a regular reticulate pattern, particularly on gastric and branchial regions. Anterolateral margin poorly divided into low lobes, last lobe most definite. Anterior thoracic sternum moderately eroded, with somewhat reticulate sculpturing. G 
<number box="[702,712,1461,1485]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
long and slender, apex somewhat tapering and devoid of setae, studded with spiniform granules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1209,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1533,1557]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
Alphonse 
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards" box="[440,698,1533,1557]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1869) Description de quelques especes nouvelles de Crustaces provenant du voyage de M. A. Bouvier aux iles Cap Vert. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie Pure et Appliquee, (ser. 2) 21, 350 - 355." type="journal article" year="1869">
Milne-Edwards (
<number box="[632,691,1533,1557]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1869.0">1869</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[824,1011,1533,1557]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Xantho" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrosus">
<emphasis box="[824,1011,1533,1557]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Xantho corrosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1210,1533,1557]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
Island, in the 
<collectingCountry name="Cape Verde" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Archipelago, and later (
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards" box="[486,757,1569,1593]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1879) Etudes sur les Crustaces Podophthalmaires de la region mexicaine. In: Mission scientifique du Mexique, Recherches zoologiques pour servir a l'histoire de la faune de Amerique Centrale et du Mexique, (5) 1, 225 - 312, pls. 40 - 54." type="journal article" year="1879">
A. Milne-Edwards 
<number box="[700,757,1569,1593]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1879.0">1879</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) he transferred it to his new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1309,1569,1593]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Glyptoxanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1309,1569,1593]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Glyptoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is easily distinguished from a sympatric species, 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1878" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1878" box="[599,1062,1605,1629]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Glyptoxanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernosus">
<emphasis box="[599,756,1606,1629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">G. cavernosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards" box="[771,1053,1605,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1878) Description de quelques especes nouvelles de Crustaces provenant du voyage aux iles Cap-Vert de MM. Bouvier et de Cessac. Bulletin de la Societe philomatique (Paris), (ser. 7), 2, 225 - 232." type="journal article" year="1878">
A. Milne-Edwards, 
<number box="[994,1053,1605,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1878.0">1878</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and from other congeners by the unique sculpturing of the dorsal carapace: i.e. fused carapace subregions, anastomosing and reticulate pattern of vermiculations, and wide and deep cervical and branchio-cardiac grooves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1209,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,668,1713,1738]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Ecology and geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[677,946,1713,1737]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Glyptoxanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corrosus">
<emphasis box="[677,946,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Glyptoxanthus corrosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a singular and rare species, only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[253,301,1750,1774]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
specimen, which is from 
<collectingCountry box="[590,723,1749,1773]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
, off the northwestern coast of Africa. Very little is known about the biology of this species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[503,648,1785,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" refString="Guinot, D. (1979) Donnees nouvelles sur la morphologie, la phylogenese et la taxonomie des Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (Paris), (A) Zoologie, 112, 1 - 354, pls. 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="1979">
Guinot 
<number box="[587,648,1785,1809]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
